Ahead of World Refugee Day on June 20th, Safe Haven wants to hear from you on how this community has positively impacted your life. Follow the hashtag #DecreaseStigmaIncreaseConnectionsForRefugees to learn more!

node.text:
TOMORROW, 1 p.m. EST: Get the latest humanitarian update from UNICEF Haiti's Chief of Communications, Ndiaga Seck, as we go live to talk about ongoing emergency relief efforts in the aftermath of the earthquake, including work with local communities and partners.

Have questions for Ndiaga? Share yours in the comments below and we may ask them during the interview!

In Monte Sinaí, Guayaquil, Ecuador, Magdalena works as a community health monitor in her neighborhood — frequently visiting her neighbors to note any medical news in the family.

With the community health monitor program, UNICEF and partners rely on local professionals and their expertise to focus on prevention and identification of #COVID19 cases. #ForEveryChild, community.

With heroes like Birma, we can #EndThePandemic.
